answers.body_markdown:
you could achieve the same result, by this way without using infer.

    import { Pipe, PipeTransform } from &quot;@angular/core&quot;;
    import { isObservable, Observable, of as just } from &quot;rxjs&quot;;
    
    @Pipe({
      name: &quot;toObservable&quot;
    })
    export class ToObservablePipe implements PipeTransform {
      transform&lt;T&gt;(value: T): T | Observable&lt;T&gt; {
        return isObservable(value) ? value : just(value);
      }
    }

but if you want to use infer, I can suggest you this solution

    import { Pipe, PipeTransform } from &quot;@angular/core&quot;;
    import { isObservable, Observable, of as just } from &quot;rxjs&quot;;
    
    type Unobservable&lt;T&gt; = T extends Observable&lt;infer R&gt; ? R : T;
    type ObservableOrAny&lt;T&gt; = Observable&lt;T&gt; | T;
    
    @Pipe({
      name: &quot;toObservable&quot;
    })
    export class ToObservablePipe implements PipeTransform {
      transform&lt;T&gt;(value: ObservableOrAny&lt;T&gt;): Observable&lt;Unobservable&lt;ObservableOrAny&lt;T&gt;&gt;&gt; {
        return isObservable(value) ? value : just(value);
      }
    }

    type Unobservable&lt;T&gt; = T extends Observable&lt;infer R&gt; ? R : T;

Means `Unobservable` could be passed `&lt;T&gt;`&#39;s type, or `any` since `R` can be some unknown type.

And here `transform&lt;T&gt;(value: T): Observable&lt;Unobservable&lt;T&gt;&gt;` You expect the return to be the same type as transform&lt;T&gt;, and that wont always be the case since we are declaring it can be `any` type and ask to infer it.

To make what you have work, type transform response to any.

    Observable&lt;Unobservable&lt;any&gt;&gt;

Unobservable in the end is just any type, I don understand the use for it.

    import { Pipe, PipeTransform } from &quot;@angular/core&quot;;
    import { isObservable, Observable, of as just } from &quot;rxjs&quot;;

    type Unobservable&lt;T&gt; = T extends Observable&lt;infer R&gt; ? R : T;

    @Pipe({
      name: &quot;toObservable&quot;
    })
    export class ToObservablePipe implements PipeTransform {
      transform&lt;T&gt;(value: T): Observable&lt;Unobservable&lt;T&gt;&gt; {
        return isObservable(value) ? value as Observable&lt;Unobservable&lt;T&gt;&gt; : 
    just(value) as Observable&lt;Unobservable&lt;T&gt;&gt;;
      }
    }

Casting will satisfy compiler if it is all you want.

